<ety>[NL. <ets>condyloma</ets>, fr. Gr. <?/, from <grk>ko`ndylos</grk>
knuckle. See <er>-oma</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A wartlike new
growth on the outer skin or adjoining mucous membrane.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ There are two kinds of condylomata, the pointed and the
broad, the latter being of syphilitic origin.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

